    • addUser

      public static void addUser(String buttonInput)
      Adds a new user to the system with the given name and adds default balance to each added user. Data is saved to hashmap.
      Parameters:
      buttonInput - The name of the user to be added, passed from GUI after user prompt.

    • deleteUser

      public static void deleteUser(String buttonInput)
      This method deletes a user account from the bank system. It takes the user account name as input parameter. The method first reads the account details from the file into a HashMap. It then prompts the user for the user account name to be deleted. If the user account name is found in the HashMap, it is removed. The changes are then written back to the file.
      Parameters:
      buttonInput - The user account name to be deleted, passed on from GUI after user prompt.

    • addMoney

      public static void addMoney(String userFromGui, Double amountFromGui)
      Adds money to a specified user account in the bank system. The account balance in the HashMap is updated with the added amount. The changes are then written back to the file.
      Parameters:
      userFromGui - The user account name to which money should be added.
      amountFromGui - The amount to add to the user account.

    • readFile

      public static void readFile()

    • withdrawMoney

      public static void withdrawMoney(String userFromGui, Double amountFromGui)
      This method withdraws money from a specified user account in the bank system. If the account has sufficient balance to cover the withdrawal amount, the account balance is updated in the HashMap and the changes are written back to the file. If the account does not have sufficient balance, an error message is displayed.
      Parameters:
      userFromGui - The user account name from which to withdraw money, passed from GUI.
      amountFromGui - The amount to withdraw from the user account, passed from GUI.

    • transferMoney

      public static void transferMoney(String senderFromGui, String recipientFromGui, Double amountFromGui)
      Transfers money between sender and recipient accounts based on the provided information.
      Parameters:
      senderFromGui - The sender's account name passed from the graphical user interface (GUI).
      recipientFromGui - The recipient's account name passed from the graphical user interface (GUI).
      amountFromGui - The amount of money to be transferred passed from the graphical user interface (GUI).
